ğŸ“Œ 5ï¸âƒ£ Data Quality Checks
âœ” Missing Values
df.isnull().sum()

âœ” Duplicate Records
df.duplicated().sum()

âœ” Logical Consistency Check
df['Expected_Revenue'] = df['Quantity'] * df['Unit_Price'] * (1 - df['Discount_Rate'])

df[['Revenue', 'Expected_Revenue']]

## Data Quality Findings

- No duplicate records detected
- Revenue calculations appear consistent with pricing logic

ğŸ“Œ 6ï¸âƒ£ Feature Engineering (CRITICAL FOR PORTFOLIO)

Raw datasets are weak.

Derived metrics = Analyst thinking.

âœ” Profit Margin
df['Margin'] = df['Profit'] / df['Revenue']

âœ” Discount Value
df['Discount_Value'] = df['Unit_Price'] * df['Discount_Rate']

## Engineered Features

- Margin â†’ Profitability efficiency indicator
- Discount_Value â†’ Absolute discount impact

ğŸ“Œ 7ï¸âƒ£ Univariate Analysis
âœ” Revenue Distribution
sns.histplot(df['Revenue'], kde=True)
plt.title("Revenue Distribution")
plt.show()

### Insight

Revenue distribution shows variability, indicating uneven transaction sizes.

âœ” Profit Margin Spread
sns.boxplot(x=df['Margin'])
plt.title("Profit Margin Spread")
plt.show()

### Insight

Margins vary significantly, suggesting pricing or cost inconsistencies.

ğŸ“Œ 8ï¸âƒ£ Bivariate Analysis
âœ” Revenue vs Profit
sns.scatterplot(x='Revenue', y='Profit', data=df)
plt.title("Revenue vs Profit Relationship")
plt.show()

### Insight

Higher revenue does not consistently translate into higher profit.

âœ” Discount vs Margin
sns.scatterplot(x='Discount_Rate', y='Margin', data=df)
plt.title("Discount Impact on Margin")
plt.show()

### Insight

Higher discounts appear associated with margin compression.

ğŸ“Œ 9ï¸âƒ£ Group-Level Analysis
âœ” Region Performance
df.groupby('Region')[['Revenue','Profit','Margin']].mean()

âœ” Category Efficiency
df.groupby('Product_Category')[['Revenue','Profit','Margin']].mean()

âœ” Segment Behavior
df.groupby('Customer_Segment')[['Revenue','Profit','Margin']].mean()

## Aggregated Insights

- Profitability varies across product categories
- Customer segments demonstrate differing margin profiles

ğŸ“Œ ğŸ”Ÿ Correlation Analysis
corr = df[['Revenue','Profit','Quantity','Discount_Rate','Margin']].corr()

sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True)
plt.title("Correlation Matrix")
plt.show()

### Insight

Discount rates negatively correlate with profit margins.

ğŸ“Œ 1ï¸âƒ£1ï¸âƒ£ Outlier Investigation
df.sort_values(by='Revenue', ascending=False).head()

### Insight

Top revenue orders require margin validation.
High revenue may not imply strong profitability.

